 Automattic are flying in for this event, and I&#8217;m personally excited to see the track devoted to CMS use featuring case studies of current publishers.</p>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t <a href="http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/">signed up</a> yet, it&#8217;s $45 for both days, or just $25 for Sunday.  More details available on <a href="http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/">2009.newyork.wordcamp.org</a>.</p>\n<p>[ Visit <a href="http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/">WordCamp NYC 2009</a> and <a href="http://central.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp.org</a> for other WordCamps happening all over the world ]</p>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=publisherblog.automattic.com&blog=1470857&post=695&subd=wordpresspublishers&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1: